<DOC><DOCNO> AP880609-0074 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-09-88 0611EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-China-Vietnam     06-09 0150</FIRST><SECOND>PM-China-Vietnam,0156</SECOND><HEAD>China Says 12 Vietnam Soldiers Killed Or Wounded In Battles</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Chinese militiamen this month killed or wounded12 Vietnamese soldiers who intruded into Chinese territory, theofficial Xinhua News Agency said today.   The report quoted military sources as saying militiamen killedor wounded four Vietnamese special agents in Diaobao Village,Yunnan province on June 4.   Two days later four more intruders were gunned down by Chinesesoldiers who came to the aid of farmers under attack.   Another surprise attack was put down on June 7, with four moreVietnamese falling, the report said.   Xinhua did not say whether there were any Chinese casualties inthe clashes.   Chinese and Vietnamese forces have fought intermittently alongthe common border since China launched a short cross-border war in1979 to ``punish'' Vietnam for invading Cambodia.   Reports by both sides of intrusions and battles cannot beindependently confirmed.'</TEXT></DOC>